feat: Efficient request bodies, proxy large requests, speed++

* Refactored v8env bodies.
  * Cloning req/resp that include string or array buffer bodies is fast now, and skips the intermediate stream
* Response bodies from native functions (`fetch`, for example) are now smart
  * The first 1mb of bodies are included when a stream is created
  * Native bodies are sent directly to users when returned in a response (like: `return new Response(fetch("https://fly.io"))`). This is useful for proxying very large requests directly.
* For people developing on fly: v8env now supports typescript, write files in `v8env/ts/`, put types in `/v8env/ts/types/` and enjoy an actual type system.

feat: Add image API (#41)

`fly.Image` now allows image conversion and resize
operations. Supported functions:

* `resize`: http://sharp.pixelplumbing.com/en/stable/api-resize/#resize
* `crop`: http://sharp.pixelplumbing.com/en/stable/api-resize/#crop
* `embed`: http://sharp.pixelplumbing.com/en/stable/api-resize/#embed
* `background`: http://sharp.pixelplumbing.com/en/stable/api-colour/#background
* `webp`: http://sharp.pixelplumbing.com/en/stable/api-output/#webp
* `png`: http://sharp.pixelplumbing.com/en/stable/api-output/#png

Run `toBuffer` to get a raw `ArrayBuffer`, or `toImage` to get a new image instance from chained operations.
